</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="435" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="41.[1395,2603,728,1589]" pageId="41" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1397,1746,1397,1430]" pageId="41" pageNumber="435">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not assessed on The [UCN Red List. The Omoa Broad-clawed Shrew is most likely restricted to Sierra de Omoa, probably occurring in the Cusuco National Park. It is potentially at risk of habitat destruction, although additional research is needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
